COMMAND init
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py init [options]
DESCRIPTION: Initialize Cypilot config for a project

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: parent of Cypilot core)
  --cypilot-root  <path>  Explicit Cypilot core root (optional override)
  --project-name  <string>  Project name used in AGENTS.md (default: project root folder name)
  --yes  <boolean>  Do not prompt; accept defaults
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Compute changes without writing files
  --force  <boolean>  Overwrite existing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Initialization successful
  1  Error (conflicts, invalid paths, etc.)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py init
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py init --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py init --project-root . --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py init --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py init --force

RELATED:
  - @CLI.info
  - @CLI.generate-agents
---

COMMAND validate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate [--artifact <path>] [--skip-code] [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate Cypilot artifacts and code traceability. Validates structure against template, cross-references between artifacts, task statuses, and code traceability markers. By default validates both artifacts and code; use --skip-code to validate artifacts only.
WORKFLOW: design-validate, features-validate, feature-validate, prd-validate, adr-validate, code-validate

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --artifact  <path>  Path to specific Cypilot artifact (if omitted, validates all registered Cypilot artifacts)
  --skip-code  <boolean>  Skip code traceability validation (by default, code is also validated)
  --verbose  <boolean>  Print full validation report (default: compact summary)
  --output  <path>  Save validation report to file (default: stdout)
  --local-only  <boolean>  Skip cross-repo workspace validation (validate local repo only)
  --source  <string>  Target a specific workspace source for validation (uses that source's adapter context)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Validation passed
  1  File system error or no cypilot found
  2  Validation failed

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - artifacts_validated: Number of artifacts checked
  - error_count: Total errors found
  - warning_count: Total warnings found
  - code_files_scanned: Number of code files checked (when code validation enabled)
  - to_code_ids_total: IDs marked to_code="true" (FULL traceability only)
  - code_ids_found: IDs found in code markers
  - coverage: Coverage ratio (found/required)
  - next_step: Hint for agent on what to do next (when PASS)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate --skip-code
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate --artifact architecture/PRD.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate --verbose
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate --output report.json

RELATED:
  - @CLI.list-ids
  - @CLI.where-defined
  - @CLI.where-used
  - @CLI.validate-kits
  - @Workflow.design-validate
  - @Workflow.feature-validate
---

COMMAND validate-kits
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-kits [--kit <id>] [--template <path>] [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate Cypilot kit configuration and template files. Checks kit definitions in artifacts.toml and validates template frontmatter, paired markers, and valid marker types/attributes. (Legacy alias: validate-rules; legacy flag alias: --rule)
WORKFLOW: kits

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <id>  Kit ID to validate (if omitted, validates all kits)
  --template  <path>  Path to specific template file to validate
  --verbose  <boolean>  Print full validation report

EXIT CODES:
  0  Validation passed
  1  File system error or no cypilot found
  2  Validation failed

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - templates_validated: Number of templates checked
  - error_count: Total errors found
  - failed_templates: (non-verbose) List of templates that failed with error_count
  - errors: List of validation errors (config issues, structure issues, unclosed markers, etc.)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-kits
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-kits --kit cypilot-sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-kits --template templates/PRD.template.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-kits --verbose

RELATED:
  - @CLI.validate
  - @Workflow.rules
---

COMMAND list-ids
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids [--artifact <path>] [options]
DESCRIPTION: List all Cypilot IDs from artifacts using template-based parsing. If no artifact is specified, scans all Cypilot-format artifacts registered in the config. Use --include-code to also scan code files for Cypilot marker references.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --artifact  <path>  Path to Cypilot artifact file (optional - if omitted, scans all registered Cypilot artifacts)
  --pattern  <string>  Filter IDs by substring or regex pattern
  --regex  <boolean>  Treat pattern as regular expression
  --kind  <string>  Filter by ID kind from template markers (e.g., 'requirement', 'spec', 'actor')
  --all  <boolean>  Include duplicate IDs in results
  --include-code  <boolean>  Also scan code files for Cypilot marker references
  --source  <string>  Filter by workspace source name (workspace mode only)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Success
  1  File system error, artifact not found, or no cypilot found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - count: Number of IDs found
  - artifacts_scanned: Number of artifacts scanned
  - code_files_scanned: Number of code files scanned (when --include-code)
  - ids: List of ID objects with id, kind, type, artifact_type, line, artifact, checked

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids --artifact architecture/PRD.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids --pattern "-actor-"
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids --kind requirement
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids --include-code
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-ids --artifact architecture/DESIGN.md --pattern "spec-.*" --regex

RELATED:
  - @CLI.where-defined
  - @CLI.get-content
  - @CLI.validate
---

COMMAND list-id-kinds
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-id-kinds [--artifact <path>]
DESCRIPTION: List ID kinds that actually exist in artifacts. Parses artifacts against their templates and returns only kinds that have at least one ID definition.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --artifact  <path>  Scan specific artifact (if omitted, scans all registered Cypilot artifacts)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Success
  1  File system error, no cypilot found, or artifact not in registry

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - kinds: List of ID kinds found in artifact(s)
  - kind_counts: Mapping of kind -> count of IDs
  - kind_to_templates: Mapping of kind -> list of template types where found
  - template_to_kinds: Mapping of template type -> list of kinds found
  - artifacts_scanned: Number of artifacts scanned

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-id-kinds
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py list-id-kinds --artifact architecture/PRD.md

RELATED:
  - @CLI.list-ids
---

COMMAND get-content
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py get-content (--artifact <path> | --code <path>) --id <string> [--inst <string>]
DESCRIPTION: Get content block for a specific Cypilot ID. Works with both artifacts (template-based parsing) and code files (Cypilot marker parsing).

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --artifact  <path>  Path to Cypilot artifact file (mutually exclusive with --code)
  --code  <path>  Path to code file (mutually exclusive with --artifact)
  --id  <string>  required  Cypilot ID to retrieve content for
  --inst  <string>  Instruction ID for code blocks (e.g., 'inst-validate-input')

EXIT CODES:
  0  Success
  1  File system error or file not found
  2  ID not found

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py get-content --artifact architecture/PRD.md --id cpt-myapp-actor-admin
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py get-content --artifact architecture/DESIGN.md --id cpt-myapp-req-auth
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py get-content --code src/auth.py --id cpt-myapp-feature-auth-flow-login
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py get-content --code src/auth.py --id cpt-myapp-feature-auth-flow-login --inst inst-validate-creds

RELATED:
  - @CLI.list-ids
  - @CLI.validate
