COMMAND info
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py info [options]
DESCRIPTION: Discover Cypilot configuration and location in a project

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --root  <path>  Project root directory to search from (default: current directory)
  --cypilot-root  <path>  Known Cypilot core location for enhanced validation

EXIT CODES:
  0  Cypilot found
  1  File system error
  2  Cypilot not found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: FOUND or NOT_FOUND
  - project_root: Resolved project root path
  - cypilot_dir: Resolved Cypilot directory path
  - project_name: Name derived from project root directory
  - kit_details: Per-kit metadata (version, content_dirs, artifact_kinds, workflows, resources)
  - artifacts_registry: Parsed artifacts.toml contents
  - agent_integrations: List of detected agent installations
  - directories: Health check of .core/, .gen/, config/ directories
  - variables: Flat dict mapping all template variable names to absolute paths (for format_map substitution)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py info
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py info --root /path/to/project
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py info --root . --cypilot-root ../Cypilot

RELATED:
  - @CLI.init
  - @CLI.resolve-vars
  - @CLI.generate-agents
---

COMMAND resolve-vars
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py resolve-vars [options]
DESCRIPTION: Resolve all template variables ({adr_template}, {scripts}, {cypilot_path}, etc.) to absolute file paths. Sources: system variables (cypilot_path, project_root) merged with kit resource bindings from core.toml. Use --kit to filter to a single kit. Use --flat for a plain variable-to-path dict.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --root  <path>  Project root directory to search from (default: current directory)
  --kit  <string>  Filter to a specific kit slug
  --flat  <boolean>  Output only the flat variables dict (default: structured output)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Variables resolved successfully
  1  Error (no project root, no cypilot directory, or kit not found)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: OK or ERROR
  - system: System-level variables (cypilot_path, project_root)
  - kits: Per-kit resource variables {slug: {var: path}}
  - variables: Flat merged dict of all variables for format_map() substitution
  When --flat, outputs only the flat variables dict (no status key).

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py resolve-vars
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py resolve-vars --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py resolve-vars --flat
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py resolve-vars --root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.info
---

COMMAND where-defined
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py where-defined --id <id> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Find where an Cypilot ID is defined using template-based parsing. Scans all registered Cypilot artifacts.

ARGUMENTS:
  id  <string>  required  Cypilot ID to find definition for

OPTIONS:
  --artifact  <path>  Limit search to specific artifact (optional)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Exactly one definition found, or no artifacts available to scan (NO_ARTIFACTS)
  1  File system error or no cypilot found
  2  ID not found after scanning (NOT_FOUND) or ambiguous (multiple definitions)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py where-defined --id cpt-myapp-actor-admin
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py where-defined --id cpt-myapp-req-auth
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py where-defined --id cpt-myapp-feature-auth --artifact architecture/DECOMPOSITION.md

RELATED:
