COMMAND kit install
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Install a kit from a local source directory. The source must contain a blueprints/ directory with at least one .md file. Copies blueprints and scripts to reference and config directories, generates resources.

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <path>  required  Path to kit source directory (must contain blueprints/)

OPTIONS:
  --force  <boolean>  Overwrite existing kit
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Installation successful
  1  Error (no project root, no cypilot directory)
  2  Invalid source or kit already installed

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - action: installed
  - kit: Kit slug
  - version: Kit version
  - files_written: Number of generated files
  - artifact_kinds: List of artifact kinds generated

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install /path/to/my-kit
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install ./kits/sdlc --force
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install ./kits/sdlc --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.kit-migrate
  - @CLI.generate-resources
---

COMMAND kit update
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update [options]
DESCRIPTION: Update installed kits. Regenerates .gen/ outputs from user blueprints. With --force, overwrites user blueprints with reference copies first.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug to update (default: all)
  --force  <boolean>  Force overwrite user blueprints with reference copies
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Update successful
  2  No kits installed or kit not found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or WARN
  - kits_updated: Number of kits updated
  - results: Per-kit results with action and files_written
  - errors: List of errors (if any)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --force
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-migrate
  - @CLI.generate-resources
---

COMMAND kit migrate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate [options]
DESCRIPTION: Migrate kit blueprints to latest versions from reference using marker-level three-way merge. Compares reference and user blueprints at the @cpt: marker level, prompts for per-marker accept/decline decisions (updates, insertions, deletions, restorations), and regenerates .gen/ after migration.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug to migrate (default: all)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files
  --no-interactive  <boolean>  Disable interactive prompts (auto-skip customized markers)
  -y, --yes  <boolean>  Auto-approve all prompts (no interaction)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Migration successful (or no migration needed)
  2  No kits installed or kit not found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, FAIL, or ABORTED
  - kits_migrated: Number of kits migrated
  - kits_current: Number of kits already up to date
  - kits_aborted: Number of kits where migration was aborted (if any)
  - results: Per-kit results with blueprint-level details
  - dry_run: Whether dry-run mode was used (if true)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --no-interactive

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND generate-resources
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources [options]
DESCRIPTION: Regenerate kit resources from user blueprints. Processes @cpt: markers in blueprint files to produce templates, rules, checklists, examples, workflows, constraints, and SKILL.md in .gen/kits/{slug}/.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug (default: all)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Generation successful
  2  No kits with blueprints found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or WARN
  - kits_processed: Number of kits processed
  - results: Per-kit results with files_written and artifact_kinds
  - errors: List of errors (if any)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND migrate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate [options]
DESCRIPTION: Migrate a v2 Cypilot project to v3. Converts adapter-based layout to blueprint-based three-directory layout (.core/, .gen/, config/), migrates artifacts.json to artifacts.toml, converts AGENTS.md format, installs kits, and validates migration.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: current directory)
  --install-dir  <string>  Cypilot directory relative to project root (default: derived from v2 core path)
  --yes  <boolean>  Skip confirmation prompt
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Detect and show plan only

EXIT CODES:
  0  Migration successful, dry-run complete, or cancelled by user
  1  Error (detection failed, migration failed)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, DRY_RUN, CANCELLED, or ERROR
  - Migration details (steps performed, files converted, etc.)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --project-root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.migrate-config
  - @CLI.init
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND migrate-config
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config [options]
DESCRIPTION: Convert remaining legacy JSON config files to TOML format. Scans for .json config files in the Cypilot directory and converts them to .toml equivalents.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: current directory)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Conversion complete

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - converted_count: Number of files converted
  - skipped_count: Number of files skipped
  - converted: List of converted file paths
  - skipped: List of skipped file paths

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config --project-root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.migrate
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND workspace-init
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init [--root <path>] [--output <path>] [--inline] [--force] [--max-depth <N>] [--dry-run]
DESCRIPTION: Initialize a multi-repo workspace by scanning nested sub-directories for repos with cypilot directories (.git or AGENTS.md marker). Generates a standalone .cypilot-workspace.toml or inline [workspace] section in config/core.toml. Creates an empty workspace when no nested repos are found, allowing incremental source addition via workspace-add.
WORKFLOW: workspace

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --root  <path>  Directory to scan for nested repos (default: current project root)
  --output  <path>  Output path for standalone workspace file
  --inline  <boolean>  Write workspace config inline into config/core.toml instead of standalone file
  --force  <boolean>  Force reinitialization when a workspace config already exists
  --max-depth  <integer>  Maximum directory depth for nested repo scanning (default: 3, min: 1). Symlinks are skipped.
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Preview discovered sources without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Workspace config created (with or without sources) or dry-run completed
  1  Error (no project root, scan root not found, cross-type conflict, existing workspace without --force)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: CREATED or DRY_RUN
  - message: Human-readable description
  - config_path: Path to generated workspace file (CREATED only)
  - workspace: Full workspace data object (DRY_RUN only)
  - sources_count: Number of discovered sources
  - sources: List of discovered source name strings
  - hint: Advisory message when custom --output path requires manual config entry (CREATED with --output only)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init --inline
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init --force
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-init --root ../repos

RELATED:
  - @CLI.workspace-add
  - @CLI.workspace-info
  - @CLI.info
---

COMMAND workspace-add
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --name <name> (--path <path> | --url <url>) [--branch <branch>] [--role <role>] [--adapter <path>] [--inline] [--force]
DESCRIPTION: Add a source to a workspace config. Auto-detects standalone vs inline workspace. Use --inline to force adding to config/core.toml. Rejects --inline when a standalone workspace already exists to prevent parallel configs. Git URL sources are not supported in inline mode. Returns error if source name already exists unless --force is specified.
WORKFLOW: workspace

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --name  <string>  Source name (human-readable key) [required]
  --path  <path>  Path to the source repo (relative to workspace file or project root)
  --url  <string>  Git remote URL (HTTPS or SSH) for the source
  --branch  <string>  Git branch/ref to checkout
  --role  <string>  Source role: artifacts, codebase, kits, full (default: full)
  --adapter  <path>  Path to cypilot dir within the source
  --inline  <boolean>  Add source inline to config/core.toml instead of standalone workspace file
  --force  <boolean>  Replace existing source with the same name instead of returning an error

EXIT CODES:
  0  Source added successfully
  1  Error (no project root, no workspace config, --inline conflict with standalone, Git URL with inline)
  2  Invalid arguments (missing required --path or --url, or both provided)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: ADDED
  - message: Human-readable description of the action
  - config_path: Path to workspace config file (standalone .cypilot-workspace.toml or inline core.toml)
  - source: Object with name, role (always present); path (when path-based), url (when URL-based); adapter, branch (included only when set)
  - replaced: true if an existing source was overwritten (omitted for new sources)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --name docs --path ../docs-repo --role artifacts
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --name lib --url https://gitlab.com/team/lib.git --branch main
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --inline --name docs --path ../docs-repo --role artifacts

RELATED:
  - @CLI.workspace-init
  - @CLI.workspace-info
---

COMMAND workspace-info
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-info
DESCRIPTION: Display workspace configuration, list sources, and show per-source status including cypilot directory detection, artifact counts, and reachability.
WORKFLOW: workspace

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:

EXIT CODES:
  0  Workspace info displayed
  1  Error (no project root, no workspace config)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: OK or ERROR
  - version: Workspace config version string
  - config_path: Path to workspace config file (standalone .cypilot-workspace.toml or inline core.toml)
  - is_inline: Whether workspace is inline in core.toml
  - project_root: Path to the project root directory
  - sources_count: Number of configured sources
  - sources: Array of source status objects, each with:
      - name, path, resolved_path, role, reachable, adapter_found
      - adapter: Configured adapter path (if set)
      - url, branch: Git remote info (if set)
      - artifact_count, system_count: Counts from adapter metadata (if reachable)
      - warning: Reason string (if source unreachable)
      - metadata_error: Error string (if metadata loading failed)
  - traceability: Object with cross_repo and resolve_remote_ids booleans
  - config_warnings: Array of validation warning strings (if any)
  - context_loaded: Whether workspace context was loaded
  - reachable_sources: Number of reachable sources (if context loaded)
  - total_registered_systems: Total systems across all sources (if context loaded)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-info

RELATED:
  - @CLI.workspace-init
  - @CLI.workspace-add
  - @CLI.workspace-sync
  - @CLI.validate
---

COMMAND delegate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py delegate <plan_dir> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Compile a Cypilot plan and delegate to ralphex for autonomous execution. Discovers ralphex, validates availability, exports the plan, and invokes the delegation command. Supports dry-run mode to assemble the command without invoking.

ARGUMENTS:
  plan_dir  <path>  required  Path to the Cypilot plan directory containing plan.toml

OPTIONS:
  --mode  <string>  Delegation mode: execute, tasks-only, or review (default: execute)
  --worktree  <boolean>  Request worktree isolation (execute and tasks-only only)
  --serve / --no-serve  <boolean>  Enable or disable dashboard serving (default: True)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Assemble the command without invoking ralphex
  --default-branch  <string>  Default branch for review precondition (default: main)
  --plans-dir  <path>  Override plans directory (highest precedence)
  --root  <path>  Project root directory (default: current directory)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Delegation successful (or dry-run command assembled)
  1  Input error (missing plan directory, missing plan.toml, invalid root)
  2  Delegation error (ralphex not found, validation failed, ralphex non-zero exit)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: ready (dry-run), delegated (success), or error
  - ralphex_path: Discovered ralphex executable path
  - validation: Ralphex availability validation result
  - bootstrap: Bootstrap gate check result
  - plan_file: Path to the written exported plan
  - command: Assembled delegation command list
  - mode: Delegation mode used
  - lifecycle_state: Final lifecycle state
  - error: Error message (when status is error)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py delegate .bootstrap/.plans/my-plan --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py delegate .bootstrap/.plans/my-plan --mode tasks-only
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py delegate .bootstrap/.plans/my-plan --worktree --serve
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py delegate .bootstrap/.plans/my-plan --root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.validate
  - @CLI.info
---

COMMAND workspace-sync
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-sync [--source <name>] [--dry-run] [--force]
DESCRIPTION: Fetch and update worktrees for Git URL workspace sources. Iterates all sources with a url field (or a single --source) and runs git fetch + checkout to update the local worktree. Local path sources are skipped. Source resolution does not perform network operations for existing repos — use workspace-sync to explicitly update.
WORKFLOW: workspace

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --source  <string>  Sync only the named source (default: all Git URL sources)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show which sources would be synced without network operations
  --force  <boolean>  Skip dirty worktree check and proceed with destructive git operations

EXIT CODES:
  0  Sync completed (at least one source synced, or no Git URL sources to sync)
  1  Error (no project root, no workspace config, named source not found, named source has no Git URL)
  2  All sources failed to sync

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: OK, FAIL, or DRY_RUN
  - synced: Number of successfully synced sources (OK/FAIL only)
  - failed: Number of failed sources (OK/FAIL only)
  - results: Array of per-source result objects, each with:
      - name: Source name
      - status: "synced" or "failed"
      - error: Error message string (failed sources only)
  - sources: Array of source preview objects (DRY_RUN only), each with name, url, branch
  - message: Human-readable description (DRY_RUN and no-git-sources only)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-sync
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-sync --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-sync --source backend

RELATED:
  - @CLI.workspace-init
  - @CLI.workspace-add
  - @CLI.workspace-info
---
